#   CODE-006: sniff: extract ?branch REFS-key + helpers

sniff's biggest redundancy is the `?<branch>` REFS-key builder pasted ~14 times in POST.c; plus SNIFFSubBasename hand-rolls path-basename, two dirty-scan callbacks duplicate, del_collect_descendants does ptr-arith name scanning, and three blocks re-resolve the wt's current branch. Factor a REFS-key helper and a current-branch resolver; route basename through abc/PATH.

##  Issues

A 14x REFS-key builder, twin dirty callbacks, and triplicated branch resolution.

 -  `?<branch>` key build (a_pad/u8bFeed1('?')/u8bFeed/a_dup) pasted ~14x: POST.c:1315,1584,1950,2157,2544,3036 +.
 -  SNIFFSubBasename (SUBS.c:47) hand-rolls last-'/' + a byte-indexed '.git' suffix; abc/PATH has basename.
 -  get_wt_dirty_cb/patch_dirty_report (GET.c:756, PATCH.c:1039) are near-identical dirty callbacks.
 -  resolve-current-branch pasted in PATCH.c:941, POST.c:1724, SNIFF.c:281.

##  Blockers

None; sniff-internal. sniff is a separate binary — rebuild the sniff target, not just be.

##  Planned

One REFS-key builder + one current-branch resolver; basename via abc/PATH.

 -  Repro first (§17): keep sniff get/post/patch tests green; add a key-build unit case.
 -  SNIFFRefKey(buf,branch) used everywhere; SNIFFCurBranch() one resolver.
 -  Basename → abc/PATH; one dirty callback shared by get/patch.

